SIMPLE: fierce
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fierce
<hw>Fierce</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Fiercer</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Fiercest</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</amorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>fers</ets>,
<ets>fiers</ets>, OF. <ets>fier</ets>, nom. <ets>fiers</ets>, fierce,
savage, cruel, F. <ets>fier</ets> proud, from L. <ets>ferus</ets> wild,
savage, cruel; perh. akin to E. <ets>bear</ets> the animal. Cf.
<er>Feral</er>, <er>Ferocity</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Furious;
violent; unrestrained; impetuous; <as>as, a <ex>fierce</ex>
wind</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His <qex>fierce</qex> thunder drove us to the deep.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Vehement in anger or cruelty; ready or eager to kill
or injure; of a nature to inspire terror; ferocious.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A
<xex>fierce</xex> whisper.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Dickens.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧A
<xex>fierce</xex> tyrant.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Pope.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>fierce</qex> foe hung upon our broken rear.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou huntest me as a <qex>fierce</qex> lion.</q> <rj><qau>Job. x.
16.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Excessively earnest, eager, or ardent.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Ferocious; savage; cruel; vehement; impetuous;
barbarous; fell. See <er>Ferocious</er>.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Fierce"ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Fierce"ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>fierceness</ent>⟦br⟧
